                                                                                                               N-envoy in charge of climate
          JAYANTH JACOB                              
	New Delhi, March 11: Shyam Saran, the Prime Ministers special envoy on the nuclear deal, has got additional work.        
	The seasoned diplomat was today named the Prime Ministers envoy on climate change.        
	Sources said Saran, a 1970-batch IFS officer, would continue to engage with Nuclear Suppliers Group countries for securing India  not a signatory to the non-proliferation treaty  a clean waiver of NSG rules for carrying out nuclear commerce.        
	They said the former foreign secretarys additional post went hand in hand with his existing office as the philosophy behind the Indo-US nuclear deal was also about access to cleaner fuel  nuclear energy.        
	Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, they added, had also spoken several times, including in Parliament, on climate change and the need for clean energy sources like nuclear power.                                                                                                                                                                            
